<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2835] CFMetadata don&apos;t set the default for Replicate_on_write correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2835</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Replicate_on_write &lt;b&gt;must&lt;/b&gt; default to true (defaulting to false is very dangerous and imho, the option of setting it to false shouldn&apos;t exist in the first place) and CFMetadata.DEFAULT_REPLICATE_ON_WRITE is correctly true. But it doesn&apos;t get set correctly. Instead, the code force the value of the cf_def even if it wasn&apos;t defined, resulting in setting it to false since that is the default value for a boolean in JAVA.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
